Some Eastern Cape villages have received the emergency tanks promised by national government but the tanks are empty. Courtesy #DStv403 MBIZANA - Some Eastern Cape villages have received the emergency tanks promised by national government but the tanks are empty. Residents say the first and last time the tanks had water was when they were delivered. Besides, the tanks in Mbizana and Ntabankulu in the Alfred Nzo District are incorrectly installed. READ: UIF COVID-19 relief fund: Employees to get paid directly eNCA reporter Dasen Thathiah brings you the full story in the video above. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.